{
  "name": "POST_UpdateTerminationProtection",
  "description": "<p>Updates termination protection for the specified stack. If a user attempts to delete a stack with termination protection enabled, the operation fails and the stack remains unchanged. For more information, see <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/using-cfn-protect-stacks.html\">Protecting a Stack From Being Deleted</a> in the <i>CloudFormation User Guide</i>.</p> <p>For <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/using-cfn-nested-stacks.html\">nested stacks</a>, termination protection is set on the root stack and can't be changed directly on the nested stack.</p>",
  "parameters": {
